You're building an application inventory management system for a US-based property and casualty insurance company that offers auto and other insurance products. The goal is to create a dynamic front-end interface where users (mainly CIOs) can filter and analyze the technology stack used across various applications, assessing whether the technologies in use are up to date or need attention.

Data Structure:

Application Inventory Table (50 records)

Columns: Application Inventory Number (FK to Technology Table),Application Name, Short Description,CIO Name,Director Name,Technologies Used (List of technologies with versions),Business Disposition, Technology Disposition, Product Line, Additional relevant fields

Technology Table 

Columns: Application Inventory Number (Primary Key),Technology Classification (e.g., Cloud, Data Warehousing, Full Stack, AI, etc.),
Technology Name((It should match Technologiesused column in Application Inventory with different versions for 50% of records),
Old Version Number,Stable Version Number,New Version Number

Key Functionality:

Tech Risk Evaluation: For each application, compare the technology versions used with the latest stable versions and categorize them as:

High Risk: If using an outdated version.

Medium Risk: If using a stable but not the latest version.

No Risk: If using the latest version.

Frontend Dashboard (ReactJS + HTML):

Provide filters to select:  CIO Name,Director Name,Department,Application Name,Product Line

Based on the filter selections, generate a report that shows the following columns from the Application Inventory table:

CIO Name,Director Name,Department,Application Name,Product Line,Technology Name,Multiple Technologies with Versions

Additionally, pull in technology risk data from the Technology Table: Old Version Number, Stable Version Number, New Version Number

Display risk status as High, Medium, or Excellent based on version comparison and 

The purpose of this system is to help CIOs quickly understand if their technology stacks are outdated, stable, or up-to-date based on the latest standards, helping in decision-making. Generate technology information data to target distribution: 30% High, 40% Medium, 30% No Risk.Highlight High risk in Red, medium in amber and No risk in Green colour Make the streamlit UI screen more attractive
